The paper proposes a novel encoding/transmission scheme for improving the performance of spatially coupled low-density parity-check (SC-LDPC) codes. This involves connecting multiple chains in a layered format, which is likely to fall under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The proposed scheme also involves transmission and decoding, which could also be relevant to networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) and control systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper discusses the design of CC schemes for different SC-LDPC code ensembles, which could be related to computer communications (cs.CC) and multimedia (cs.MM).
